  VERSION="4"
 CATEGORY="network"
ATTRIBUTE="server"
   SOURCE="portmap_$VERSION"
      URL="ftp://ftp.porcupine.org/pub/security/index.html"
 HOMEPAGE="ftp://ftp.porcupine.org/pub/security"
      REQ="tcp_wrappers"
    SHORT="portmap manages RPC connections, which are used by NFS and NIS protocols."
cat << EOF
The portmapper manages RPC connections, which are used by protocols 
such as NFS and NIS.  The portmap server must be running on machines
which act as servers for protocols which make use of the RPC mechanism.
This portmapper supports hosts.{allow,deny} type access control.
EOF
